<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-12T18:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-12T18:30:00-05:00" n="59" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">856B.20/25: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Aruba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Standish</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aruba</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-12T19:00:00-04:30">January
                                    12, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received January 13—1:46 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>15. A detachment Air Corps landed 10 a.m. today without incident. Dutch
                            and British cooperated fully.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Standish</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>